    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="BB16HKA" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>16HKA - Instrument Cluster - Omit Fault Codes</title>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">FEATURE CODE DESCRIPTION:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>16HKA - IP CLUSTER DISPLAY OMIT FAULT CODES - Omit display of fault codes in instrument cluster and
            disable blink codes (requires service tool to retrieve and view fault codes).
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">FEATURE / BODY FUNCTION:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>Optional feature that removes the ability to read fault codes inside the vehicle, using the cluster's LCD
            display. No hardware change is needed. This is a software configurable feature.
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">SOFTWARE FEATURE CODES / PROGRAMMABLE PARAMETERS:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>16HKA (IP Cluster Display Omit Fault Codes): 595ANV</para>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">WIRING INFORMATION:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>No additional wiring is needed.</para>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Set Park Brake</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Press and hold "Cruise On" switch and "Cruise Resume" switch</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Odometer should
                    <emph type="bold">NOT</emph>
                    display "NO FAULTS" or a number of FAULTS.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">HOW TO ADD THESE FEATURES:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>Select software feature code 595ANV using the Diamond Logic&#174; Builder software (See Local Dealer)
        </para>
    </svcproc>
